text: The Papuan pygmy mulga snake (Pseudechis rossignolii) is a venomous snake of the family Elapidae native to Australia, genetically confirmed as a distinct species in 2017. It was originally described by Raymond Hoser in 2000 as Pailsus rossignolii, naming it for Victorian snake handler Fred Rossignoli. == References == Category:Elapidae Category:Reptiles described in 2000
title: Papuan pygmy mulga snake
